WEBVTT

01:38.098 --> 01:39.765
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

01:39.933 --> 01:41.058
MARY?

01:41.226 --> 01:43.936
I WANT YOU TO HEAR ME OUT
WITHOUT ANY INTERRUPTING.

01:44.104 --> 01:47.815
YOU AND I HAVE KNOWN
EACH OTHER HOW LONG?
ALMOST A YEAR?

01:47.982 --> 01:50.192
WELL, IT'S TAKEN ME THAT
LONG TO GET UP THE NERVE

01:50.360 --> 01:52.736
TO SAY WHAT I'M
GOING TO SAY NOW.

01:52.904 --> 01:54.780
YOU KNOW
HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU.

01:54.948 --> 01:56.824
I KNOW THAT YOU LOVE ME,

01:56.991 --> 01:59.409
AND WE COULD HAVE
A PERFECT LIFE TOGETHER.

01:59.577 --> 02:03.288
OUR INTERESTS ARE THE SAME,
AND WE TEACH TOGETHER.

02:03.456 --> 02:07.626
WHAT I'M TRYING TO SAY IS,
WILL YOU BE MY WIFE?

02:27.814 --> 02:28.814
MARY?

02:28.982 --> 02:30.399
COME IN.

02:30.567 --> 02:34.319
MARY, I WANT YOU TO
HEAR ME OUT WITHOUT
ANY INTERRUPTIONS.

02:34.487 --> 02:36.071
CERTAINLY.

02:40.285 --> 02:42.286
I HAVE TO GO
TO THE POST OFFICE.

02:42.453 --> 02:44.329
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

02:57.218 --> 02:59.386
COME ON, KENDALL.

02:59.554 --> 03:02.097
YOU GOT TO DO IT.

03:10.857 --> 03:12.065
MARY?

03:12.233 --> 03:13.650
COME IN.

03:18.406 --> 03:19.781
MARY...

03:19.949 --> 03:21.491
ADAM,
WHATEVER IT IS,

03:21.659 --> 03:23.660
I PROMISE YOU
I WON'T INTERRUPT.

03:23.828 --> 03:25.495
I JUST HOPE IT'S
MORE IMPORTANT

03:25.663 --> 03:27.706
THAN TELLING ME
YOU'RE GOING TO
THE POST OFFICE.

03:27.874 --> 03:30.334
WELL, IT IS.
IT'S, UM...

03:32.003 --> 03:33.795
IT'S, UM...

03:34.964 --> 03:37.299
WELL, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT. IT...

03:39.010 --> 03:40.928
YOU KNOW, THE SCHOOL'S
GETTING WAY TOO CROWDED,

03:41.095 --> 03:43.847
AND I THINK YOU SHOULD
GIVE UP YOUR ROOM.

03:44.015 --> 03:46.642
AND GO WHERE?

03:48.144 --> 03:50.103
INTO MY ROOM?

03:50.271 --> 03:52.522
ADAM KENDALL,
THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

03:52.690 --> 03:54.191
IT'S NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE FUNNY.

03:54.359 --> 03:57.027
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
A PROPOSAL.

04:05.620 --> 04:08.956
IT'S THE MOST
RIDICULOUS PROPOSAL
I'VE EVER HEARD.

04:10.667 --> 04:13.377
I SHOULD HAVE GONE
TO THE POST OFFICE.

04:24.639 --> 04:27.099
WHY DON'T
WE BOTH GO? I...

04:27.267 --> 04:29.893
I WANT TO SEND
A TELEGRAM TO MA AND PA

04:30.061 --> 04:32.980
AND TELL THEM WE'RE
GETTING MARRIED.

04:33.147 --> 04:34.940
OH...I...

04:37.193 --> 04:38.986
HA HA HA!

04:40.071 --> 04:42.322
OH! I LOVE YOU!

04:42.490 --> 04:44.992
I LOVE YOU. HA HA!

04:52.625 --> 04:55.168
WHOA!

04:55.336 --> 04:56.795
CAROLINE!

04:56.963 --> 04:58.422
Charles: CAROLINE!

04:58.589 --> 05:01.174
CHARLES, WHAT'S WRONG?

05:01.342 --> 05:03.135
TELEGRAM FROM MARY.

05:03.303 --> 05:04.678
WHAT IS IT?

05:04.846 --> 05:06.305
JUST READ IT.

05:07.932 --> 05:10.392
[DOG BARKING]

05:10.560 --> 05:12.227
Laura:
PA, WHAT IS IT?

05:12.395 --> 05:14.688
YOU BEST LET
YOUR MA TELL YOU.

05:14.856 --> 05:16.398
OH, MY GOODNESS!

05:16.566 --> 05:18.358
WHAT IS IT, MA?

05:19.777 --> 05:21.486
MY BABY'S
GETTING MARRIED.

05:21.654 --> 05:22.946
GRACE?

05:23.114 --> 05:25.115
NO, SILLY. MARY.

05:25.283 --> 05:27.659
I KNEW IT.
I JUST KNEW IT!

05:27.827 --> 05:28.952
WHEN IS IT, MA?

05:29.120 --> 05:31.371
AUGUST 15th...
IN WINOKA.

05:31.539 --> 05:33.623
OH, CHARLES,
THAT'S ONLY 3 WEEKS AWAY.

05:33.791 --> 05:34.916
HOW WILL WE EVER
GET READY--

05:35.084 --> 05:36.793
WE'LL MANAGE,
WE'LL MANAGE.

05:36.961 --> 05:37.961
CAN WE ALL GO?

05:38.129 --> 05:39.504
Charles: WE'LL SEE.

05:39.672 --> 05:42.132
OH, CHARLES.

05:42.300 --> 05:45.302
OH! MARY'S
GETTING MARRIED.

05:46.971 --> 05:48.430
[CRYING]
THEY'RE GETTING MARRIED.

05:48.598 --> 05:50.640
HEY...TAKE IT EASY.
TAKE IT EASY.

05:50.808 --> 05:52.976
BEST GET YOU
IN THE HOUSE,
SIT DOWN,

05:53.144 --> 05:54.561
AND HAVE
A CUP OF TEA.

05:54.729 --> 05:56.104
MM-HMM.

05:59.108 --> 06:01.568
I'M NEVER
GETTING MARRIED.

06:01.736 --> 06:02.986
IT MAKES MA SAD.

06:03.154 --> 06:04.946
MA'S NOT SAD.
SHE'S HAPPY.

06:05.114 --> 06:06.907
THEN WHY
IS SHE CRYING?

06:07.075 --> 06:09.951
I JUST TOLD YOU--
BECAUSE SHE'S HAPPY.

06:10.119 --> 06:14.289
I'LL NEVER
UNDERSTAND GROWNUPS.

06:15.917 --> 06:17.667
YOU REMEMBER
HOW LONG IT TOOK US

06:17.835 --> 06:19.294
TO GET FROM WINOKA
BACK HERE?

06:19.462 --> 06:22.589
I SURE DO. IT SEEMED
LIKE WE'D NEVER
REACH WALNUT GROVE.

06:22.757 --> 06:24.299
THAT WAS BY WAGON.

06:24.467 --> 06:25.884
IF WE WENT
THE SAME WAY NOW,

06:26.052 --> 06:28.303
YOUR MA AND I
WOULD NEVER MAKE IT
IN TIME FOR THE WEDDING,

06:28.471 --> 06:30.347
SO WE'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO TAKE THE TRAIN,

06:30.515 --> 06:32.391
AND THAT'S
GOING TO COST.

06:32.558 --> 06:34.601
AND THERE'S 6 OF US.

06:34.769 --> 06:37.187
EVEN IF THEY LET
BABY GRACE ON FOR FREE,

06:37.355 --> 06:41.358
THERE'S STILL NO
WAY WE COULD AFFORD
ALL THOSE FARES.

06:41.526 --> 06:44.528
I KNOW YOU'RE DISAPPOINTED,
BUT, LAURA, YOU AND ALBERT

06:44.695 --> 06:47.197
ARE GOING TO HAVE TO
STAY HERE AND TAKE CARE
OF THE YOUNG ONES.

06:47.365 --> 06:48.990
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN MANAGE?

06:49.158 --> 06:51.618
SURE WE CAN.
WE UNDERSTAND.

06:51.786 --> 06:53.954
Carrie: I CAN TAKE CARE
OF BABY GRACE.

06:54.122 --> 06:56.373
I'VE EVEN CHANGED HER
WHEN SHE DOES TWO,

06:56.541 --> 06:58.458
AND IT REALLY
SMELLS AWFUL!

06:58.626 --> 07:00.043
Caroline: THAT'S
ENOUGH, MISS.

07:00.211 --> 07:01.586
HA HA HA!

07:01.754 --> 07:03.713
Caroline: I WISH
WE COULD ALL GO.

07:03.881 --> 07:05.924
ARE YOU SURE
YOU CAN MANAGE?

07:06.092 --> 07:07.968
IF ONLY THE GARVEYS
WEREN'T AWAY,

07:08.136 --> 07:10.929
THEY COULD STOP IN
AND CHECK ON YOU
FROM TIME TO TIME.

07:11.097 --> 07:13.056
Albert: DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL BE FINE.

07:13.224 --> 07:14.307
WON'T WE, LAURA?

07:14.475 --> 07:15.725
SURE, WE WILL.

07:15.893 --> 07:18.895
Caroline: YOU'RE
BEING VERY GROWN-UP
ABOUT IT.

07:19.063 --> 07:20.730
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

07:20.898 --> 07:22.190
SO AM I.

07:22.358 --> 07:23.650
WELL, WE GOT THAT
SETTLED.

07:23.818 --> 07:25.610
THE ONLY PROBLEM
WE HAVE NOW IS
A WEDDING PRESENT.

07:25.778 --> 07:27.737
WE'LL GO IN TO OLESON'S
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

07:27.905 --> 07:31.700
NOW...I HAVE JUST
THE THING FOR THEM,

07:31.868 --> 07:34.369
SOMETHING THEY'LL CHERISH
ALL THEIR LIVES.

07:34.537 --> 07:37.414
OH! IT'S BEEN CRAFTED
BY A TRUE ARTIST.

07:37.582 --> 07:40.333
IT ISN'T EXACTLY
WHAT I HAD IN MIND,
MRS. OLESON.

07:40.501 --> 07:41.918
IT'S VERY BEAUTIFUL,

07:42.086 --> 07:45.213
BUT I WAS THINKING
OF SOMETHING A LITTLE
MORE PRACTICAL.

07:45.381 --> 07:47.090
AHA! YES.

07:47.258 --> 07:49.968
I UNDERSTAND PERFECTLY.
YOU CAN'T AFFORD IT.

07:50.136 --> 07:53.597
HERE. I HAVE SOMETHING OVER
HERE THAT YOU MIGHT LIKE.

07:53.764 --> 07:55.557
[WHISPERING]
Charles.

08:00.396 --> 08:03.106
I SET THIS ASIDE
THE MINUTE
I GOT THE NEWS.

08:03.274 --> 08:06.651
I WANT YOU TO
GIVE THIS TO HER
WITH OUR LOVE.

08:07.862 --> 08:09.905
[CHIRPING]

08:20.666 --> 08:23.335
NELS, THAT'S BEAUTIFUL,
BUT IT'S TOO MUCH.

08:23.503 --> 08:24.794
NO, IT ISN'T.

08:24.962 --> 08:26.296
THAT LITTLE GIRL
HAS BEEN MY PET

08:26.464 --> 08:28.924
SINCE THE FIRST DAY SHE
WALKED INTO THE STORE.

08:29.091 --> 08:31.218
I WANT HER
TO REMEMBER ME.

08:32.970 --> 08:35.263
SHE WILL, EVERY TIME
SHE PLAYS IT.

08:36.807 --> 08:38.099
IF YOU DON'T MIND,

08:38.267 --> 08:40.852
I'D LIKE TO WRAP
THIS IN HERE.

08:41.020 --> 08:43.146
THE MISSIS, UM...

08:43.314 --> 08:45.190
WELL, YOU KNOW.

08:49.320 --> 08:51.279
THANK YOU, FRIEND.

08:59.622 --> 09:01.498
Charles: REVEREND.

09:01.666 --> 09:03.333
CHARLES
AND CAROLINE.

09:03.501 --> 09:05.460
WHAT IS THIS
I HEAR ABOUT MARY?

09:05.628 --> 09:07.504
WE WERE JUST COMING OVER
TO TELL YOU OURSELVES.

09:07.672 --> 09:10.840
BLESS THAT CHILD!
SHE'S NOT A CHILD
ANY LONGER, IS SHE?

09:11.008 --> 09:14.135
CONGRATULATIONS,
AND TELL MARY THAT...

09:14.303 --> 09:16.888
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

09:17.056 --> 09:18.974
WHATEVER IT IS,
I KNOW IT'S WITH
A FULL HEART,

09:19.141 --> 09:20.016
AND SHE'LL
KNOW IT, TOO.

09:20.184 --> 09:21.518
WILL IT BE IN WINOKA?

09:21.686 --> 09:24.145
Charles: YEAH.
SHE'D LIKE TO GET
MARRIED HERE BY YOU,

09:24.313 --> 09:26.106
BUT SHE JUST CAN'T
LEAVE THE SCHOOL
THAT LONG.

09:26.274 --> 09:27.649
Reverend:
WHEN'S THE DATE?

09:27.817 --> 09:29.109
AUGUST 15th.

09:29.277 --> 09:31.695
WELL, NOW,
HOLD ON HERE A MINUTE.

09:31.862 --> 09:33.196
I'LL BE IN CREIGHTON THEN.

09:33.364 --> 09:34.614
THERE'S A MINISTERS
GATHERING.

09:34.782 --> 09:36.366
IF I COULD GET AWAY
A DAY EARLY...

09:36.534 --> 09:38.201
CREIGHTON'S STILL
A LONG WAY FROM
WINOKA, REVEREND.

09:38.369 --> 09:40.829
WELL, I'VE MADE LONGER TRIPS
FOR LESS JOYOUS REASONS!

09:40.997 --> 09:42.998
OH, CHARLES,
IT WOULD MEAN
SO MUCH TO HER.

09:43.165 --> 09:45.250
NOW, IT'S SETTLED,
THEN. NO ARGUMENT.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.460
OH! REVEREND!

09:47.628 --> 09:48.920
OH!

09:49.088 --> 09:51.047
HOW CAN WE THANK YOU?

09:51.215 --> 09:55.427
WELL, I MUST SAY,
I DON'T GET THANKED
THAT WAY VERY OFTEN!

09:55.595 --> 09:57.887
BUT DON'T SAY ANYTHING
TO MARY ABOUT IT,

09:58.055 --> 09:59.556
BECAUSE, WELL,
YOU CAN'T FORESEE

09:59.724 --> 10:01.391
WHAT CIRCUMSTANCES
MIGHT ARISE.

10:01.559 --> 10:02.934
I MIGHT BE
CALLED ELSEWHERE,

10:03.102 --> 10:04.436
AND I'D HATE TO HAVE
HER DISAPPOINTED.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.521
WE WON'T SAY
A WORD TILL
YOU GET THERE.

10:06.689 --> 10:08.857
BE BETTER THAT
WAY, ANYWAY.
BE A SURPRISE.

10:09.025 --> 10:10.609
REVEREND,
THANK YOU.

10:10.776 --> 10:12.861
OH, THANK YOU!

10:13.029 --> 10:15.071
[CLANGING]

10:22.663 --> 10:24.789
[BABY CRYING]

10:32.590 --> 10:34.090
Charles:
HERE. I GOT THAT.

10:34.258 --> 10:35.592
Caroline: THANK YOU.

10:35.760 --> 10:36.926
THANK YOU, MR. OLESON.

10:37.094 --> 10:40.597
GOOD-BYE,
DARLINGS. MMM!

10:40.765 --> 10:42.474
YOU TAKE GOOD CARE.

10:42.642 --> 10:44.434
OH, AND IF THERE'S
ANY TROUBLE AT ALL,

10:44.602 --> 10:46.061
DON'T HESITATE
TO SEND A TELEGRAM.

10:46.228 --> 10:48.313
CAROLINE, NOTHING'S
GOING TO GO WRONG.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.939
THAT'S RIGHT.

10:51.525 --> 10:54.361
WELL, KEEP GRACE
AWAY FROM THE STOVE,
AND, UH--

10:54.528 --> 10:56.029
CAROLINE, WOULD YOU
LET THE CHILDREN

10:56.197 --> 10:58.782
GET OFF THE TRAIN
BEFORE IT LEAVES?

10:58.949 --> 11:00.075
GOOD-BYE.

11:00.242 --> 11:01.368
BYE.
BYE.
BYE.

11:01.535 --> 11:03.286
Charles: WE'LL SEE YOU
A WEEK FROM THURSDAY.

11:03.454 --> 11:04.996
BYE, PA.
SEND MARY OUR LOVE.

11:05.164 --> 11:06.414
Charles: NELS, THANKS
A LOT FOR THE RIDE.

11:06.582 --> 11:07.582
MY PLEASURE.

11:07.750 --> 11:08.625
BYE-BYE!

11:08.793 --> 11:10.126
Caroline: TAKE GOOD CARE!

11:10.294 --> 11:11.670
Albert: DON'T WORRY!

11:16.509 --> 11:18.093
TICKETS, PLEASE.

11:22.682 --> 11:23.723
THANK YOU.

11:23.891 --> 11:25.725
TICKETS, PLEASE.

11:27.478 --> 11:28.770
JUST GO STRAIGHT THROUGH.

11:28.938 --> 11:29.813
THANK YOU.

11:29.980 --> 11:30.730
TICKETS, PLEASE.

11:30.898 --> 11:32.816
I HATE LEAVING THEM
LIKE THIS.

11:32.983 --> 11:35.110
OH, CAROLINE.
WE'VE LEFT THEM BEFORE.

11:35.277 --> 11:37.320
NOT FOR SUCH
A LONG TIME.

11:37.488 --> 11:39.239
WELL, WE DON'T HAVE
TO GO, YOU KNOW.

11:39.407 --> 11:42.492
WE CAN ALWAYS SEND
MARY A TELEGRAM SAYING
"CONGRATULATIONS"

11:42.660 --> 11:43.993
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

11:44.161 --> 11:45.870
OH, CHARLES, STOP IT!

11:46.038 --> 11:49.082
I PROMISE I WON'T
SAY ANOTHER WORD.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.375
ALL RIGHT.

11:50.543 --> 11:52.127
OH, I HOPE THEY--

11:52.294 --> 11:53.878
THAT'S ANOTHER WORD.

11:58.801 --> 12:00.885
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

13:12.082 --> 13:14.751
I SEE HER!
MARY!

13:14.919 --> 13:16.836
MARY! ADAM!

13:17.755 --> 13:18.755
ADAM!

13:18.923 --> 13:20.298
HA HA!

13:20.466 --> 13:21.800
MARY!

13:21.967 --> 13:23.760
OH, CHARLES!

13:23.928 --> 13:25.762
HERE YOU GO.
TAKE IT EASY!

13:25.930 --> 13:27.597
OH, MARY!

13:27.765 --> 13:31.559
OH, WE'RE SO HAPPY
FOR YOU BOTH,

13:31.727 --> 13:32.894
FOR YOU TWO.

13:33.062 --> 13:35.605
OH, MARY, YOU LOOK
JUST BEAUTIFUL!

13:35.773 --> 13:37.440
YOU, TOO, ADAM.

13:37.608 --> 13:39.943
I NEVER THOUGHT OF YOU
LOOKING BEAUTIFUL, ADAM,
BUT IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

13:40.110 --> 13:42.445
THANK YOU, SIR.
YOU REMEMBER
THE REVEREND CORLISS.

13:42.613 --> 13:44.697
HELLO, CHARLES,
CAROLINE. GOOD TO
SEE YOU AGAIN.

13:44.865 --> 13:45.782
NICE SEEING YOU,
REVEREND.

13:45.950 --> 13:47.742
THE REVEREND IS
GOING TO MARRY US.

13:47.910 --> 13:49.994
I'D LIKE TO HAVE A CHANCE
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT THOSE
ARRANGEMENTS, REVEREND.

13:50.162 --> 13:51.120
FINE. ANYTIME.
THANK YOU.

13:51.288 --> 13:52.455
WHAT WOULD YOU FOLKS
LIKE TO DO NOW?

13:52.623 --> 13:53.665
I KNOW YOU MUST BE
TIRED FROM THE TRIP.

13:53.833 --> 13:55.542
WHY DON'T WE
CLEAN UP A LITTLE,

13:55.709 --> 13:58.211
REST FOR A WHILE,
AND THEN WE'LL MEET
YOU AT THE SCHOOL.

13:58.379 --> 13:59.796
FINE. WE'LL HAVE
SOME SANDWICHES READY.

13:59.964 --> 14:00.922
HEY, SOUNDS GOOD.

14:01.090 --> 14:02.423
I'LL GIVE YOU A HAND
WITH THE BAGS.

14:02.591 --> 14:04.425
IT WILL GIVE US
A CHANCE TO TALK
ABOUT THE WEDDING.

14:04.593 --> 14:06.219
APPRECIATE IT,
REVEREND.

14:06.387 --> 14:08.596
OH, MY LITTLE GIRL!

14:08.764 --> 14:09.806
OH!

14:09.974 --> 14:12.809
GOING TO BE
A MARRIED WOMAN.

14:19.817 --> 14:22.110
GET THE TUB AND THE WATER
SOON AS I GET A CHANCE.

14:22.278 --> 14:23.611
THANK YOU.

14:27.449 --> 14:29.576
THE OLD HOTEL LOOKS
ABOUT THE SAME.

14:29.743 --> 14:31.786
OH! THEY'VE LET IT
RUN DOWN SO.

14:31.954 --> 14:34.414
I DON'T THINK SO.
LOOKS ABOUT
THE SAME TO ME.

14:34.582 --> 14:37.041
THE FURNITURE
IS COVERED WITH DUST.

14:37.209 --> 14:38.167
AND LOOK AT THIS!

14:38.335 --> 14:40.503
WELL, IT'S ONLY
FOR A FEW DAYS.

14:40.671 --> 14:42.255
WE'VE LIVED
IN WORSE PLACES.

14:42.423 --> 14:45.341
IT JUST HURTS ME TO SEE
SOMETHING THAT WE TOOK
PRIDE IN NEGLECTED SO.

14:45.509 --> 14:49.429
AND THAT MANAGER--
WITH THAT SMELLY OLD CIGAR!

14:49.597 --> 14:51.180
WHEN YOU GET THROUGH
CLEANING HERE,

14:51.348 --> 14:53.516
YOU OUGHT TO GO DOWN
AND LOOK AT THE KITCHEN.

14:53.684 --> 14:55.351
I'LL BET THAT'S
REALLY A MESS.

14:55.519 --> 14:56.978
I BET IT IS.

14:57.146 --> 14:59.314
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
WHILE I'M TAKING
A NICE, LONG NAP,

14:59.481 --> 15:02.275
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
STAY DOWN THERE AND
CLEAN IT RIGHT UP?

15:04.862 --> 15:06.070
HA HA HA HA!

15:06.238 --> 15:07.655
OH!

15:13.203 --> 15:14.287
Mary: WHAT ABOUT GRACE?

15:14.455 --> 15:16.789
HAS SHE GROWN MUCH?
IS SHE CRAWLING?

15:16.957 --> 15:19.542
Caroline: OH, YES,
AND WALKING AND
INTO EVERYTHING.

15:19.710 --> 15:22.378
Charles: SHE AND YOUR
MOTHER PRACTICE MAKING
FACES AT EACH OTHER.

15:22.546 --> 15:23.713
HA HA HA!

15:23.881 --> 15:25.840
Caroline:
MARY, IT SEEMS LIKE
ONLY YESTERDAY

15:26.008 --> 15:27.258
YOU WERE AS LITTLE
AS SHE IS.

15:27.426 --> 15:28.885
JUST THINK,
ABOUT A YEAR FROM NOW,

15:29.053 --> 15:30.511
YOU'LL ALL BE
CALLING ME GRANDPA.

15:30.679 --> 15:32.096
OH, CHARLES!
DON'T RUSH THEM.

15:32.264 --> 15:33.723
OH, MAKE IT A YEAR
AND A HALF, THEN.

15:33.891 --> 15:36.768
Charles: I JUST HOPE
YOU TWO ARE AS
BLESSED AS WE WERE.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.771
I CAN REMEMBER TIMES
WHEN YOU DIDN'T
CALL IT BLESSED.

15:39.939 --> 15:42.315
I ALWAYS THOUGHT IT.
I MAY HAVE SAID
DIFFERENTLY SOMETIMES.

15:42.483 --> 15:44.651
LET'S FACE IT.
THEY DID GET INTO A LITTLE
MISCHIEF, DIDN'T THEY?

15:44.818 --> 15:47.528
WHICH ONE GAVE YOU
THE MOST TROUBLE? MARY?

15:47.696 --> 15:50.365
MMM, IT'S HARD TO SAY.
CARRIE DID LIKE THE CREEK.

15:50.532 --> 15:52.700
I DON'T KNOW HOW
MANY TIMES I HAD TO
PULL HER OUT OF THAT.

15:52.868 --> 15:55.078
I'D SAY THEY ALL KEPT
LIFE PRETTY EXCITING,
THOUGH.

15:55.245 --> 15:57.080
MMM, I'D HAVE TO
SAY MARY.

15:57.247 --> 15:59.540
MAYBE IT WAS BECAUSE
SHE WAS MY FIRST.

15:59.708 --> 16:01.459
SHE WAS
THE FASTEST RUNNER.

16:01.627 --> 16:04.796
ONE SECOND SHE'D
BE THERE, THEN I'D
TURN AROUND,

16:04.964 --> 16:06.923
SHE'D BE
A HALF A MILE
DOWN THE ROAD.

16:07.091 --> 16:08.841
Adam: MARY,
I'M SURPRISED AT YOU.

16:09.009 --> 16:12.095
Charles: I REMEMBER
A TIME--SHE WAS, WHAT,
ABOUT 2 YEARS OLD.

16:12.262 --> 16:13.554
WE WERE LIVING
IN THE BIG WOODS.

16:13.722 --> 16:15.390
DEAD OF WINTER,
SHE UP AND RUNS OFF.

16:15.557 --> 16:17.308
SNOW'S 2 FEET DEEP
ON THE GROUND.

16:17.476 --> 16:18.768
Caroline: OH, I'LL
NEVER FORGET THAT.

16:18.936 --> 16:20.645
Charles: THE WIND'S
BLOWING THAT POWDERED SNOW

16:20.813 --> 16:23.147
JUST ENOUGH TO COVER
THE TRACKS, AND WE START
SEARCHING AND SEARCHING.

16:23.315 --> 16:25.108
WE MUST HAVE BEEN
OUT THERE FOR TWO HOURS.

16:25.275 --> 16:26.776
CAROLINE WAS PREGNANT
WITH LAURA AT THE TIME.

16:26.944 --> 16:28.903
I HAD TO CONVINCE HER
TO GO BACK TO THE CABIN.

16:29.071 --> 16:30.655
WE FINALLY GET BACK,
OPEN THE DOOR,

16:30.823 --> 16:32.782
AND WHO'S SITTING RIGHT
IN FRONT OF THE FIREPLACE

16:32.950 --> 16:34.534
WITH JAM ALL OVER
HER FACE BUT MARY,

16:34.702 --> 16:36.452
JUST AS HAPPY
AS SHE COULD BE.

16:36.620 --> 16:40.707
Adam: YOU WERE
REALLY A BAD ONE,
WEREN'T YOU, MARY?

16:43.794 --> 16:45.211
Adam: MARY?

16:47.464 --> 16:49.632
WHAT? OH, I'M SORRY.

16:49.800 --> 16:52.468
I WASN'T LISTENING.
MY MIND WAS WANDERING.

16:52.636 --> 16:55.638
YOUR FATHER WAS JUST
TELLING ME ABOUT
YOUR WANDERING.

16:55.806 --> 17:00.018
I'M KIND OF TIRED.
I THINK I'LL GO
TO MY ROOM.

17:00.185 --> 17:01.853
YOU LOOK TIRED.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.896
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

17:04.064 --> 17:05.857
YES.

17:06.025 --> 17:08.026
ALL THE EXCITEMENT,
I GUESS.

17:08.193 --> 17:10.194
WELL, I THINK WE COULD
ALL USE SOME SLEEP.

17:10.362 --> 17:13.448
THAT'S IF I CAN GET
CAROLINE TO STOP CLEANING
LONG ENOUGH TO LIE DOWN.

17:13.615 --> 17:16.951
OH, CHARLES, I DECLARE,
YOU'RE WORSE THAN
THE CHILDREN EVER WERE.

17:17.119 --> 17:18.077
GOOD NIGHT, MARY.

17:18.245 --> 17:19.412
WE CAN SHOW
OURSELVES OUT.

17:19.580 --> 17:20.997
Adam: I HAVE TO
LOCK UP ANYWAY.

17:21.165 --> 17:22.331
Charles: GOOD NIGHT, HON.

17:22.499 --> 17:23.458
GOOD NIGHT, PA.

17:23.625 --> 17:24.667
Caroline:
GOOD NIGHT, ADAM.

17:24.835 --> 17:26.669
WE'LL SEE YOU
TOMORROW.

17:35.387 --> 17:37.680
MARY, ARE YOU SURE
YOU WERE JUST TIRED?

17:37.848 --> 17:39.140
I'M FINE, REALLY.

17:39.308 --> 17:41.309
THE DAY WAS JUST
TOO MUCH, I GUESS.

17:41.477 --> 17:43.019
I BEST GO TO BED.

17:43.187 --> 17:46.189
ALL RIGHT. I'M GOING TO
GO CHECK ON THE KIDS.

17:46.356 --> 17:48.399
GOOD NIGHT.

17:48.567 --> 17:49.442
SLEEP WELL.

17:49.610 --> 17:50.985
YOU, TOO.

18:06.752 --> 18:09.212
Charles: DEAD OF WINTER,
SHE UP AND RUNS OFF.

18:09.379 --> 18:11.255
SNOW'S 2 FEET DEEP
ON THE GROUND.

18:11.423 --> 18:13.382
Caroline: SHE WAS
THE FASTEST RUNNER.

18:13.550 --> 18:15.384
JUST THINK,
ABOUT A YEAR FROM NOW,

18:15.552 --> 18:17.011
YOU'LL ALL BE
CALLING ME GRANDPA.

18:17.179 --> 18:19.847
ONE SECOND SHE'D
BE THERE, THEN I'D
TURN AROUND,

18:20.015 --> 18:21.891
SHE'D BE
A HALF A MILE
DOWN THE ROAD.

18:22.059 --> 18:24.393
I JUST HOPE
YOU TWO ARE AS
BLESSED AS WE WERE.

18:24.561 --> 18:26.646
SHE WAS
THE FASTEST RUNNER.

18:26.814 --> 18:28.564
AND WE START SEARCHING
AND SEARCHING.

18:28.732 --> 18:31.067
ONE SECOND SHE'D
BE THERE, THEN I'D
TURN AROUND,

18:31.235 --> 18:34.028
SHE'D BE
A HALF A MILE
DOWN THE ROAD.

18:35.614 --> 18:37.073
[DOOR LATCH CLICKS]

19:02.432 --> 19:04.100
[PIANO PLAYING]

19:04.268 --> 19:06.686
[PEOPLE TALKING
AND LAUGHING]

19:09.398 --> 19:11.691
SOMETHING IS
BOTHERING MARY.

19:13.068 --> 19:16.070
WHAT MAKES YOU
SAY THAT?

19:16.238 --> 19:18.739
I CAN TELL.

19:20.909 --> 19:24.954
SHE SEEMED CHEERFUL
ENOUGH AT THE BEGINNING
OF THE EVENING.

19:25.122 --> 19:28.541
WELL, WHATEVER IT IS,
I'M SURE SHE'LL COME
TO YOU WITH IT.

19:28.709 --> 19:30.960
SHE ALWAYS HAS.

19:31.128 --> 19:32.879
I SUPPOSE.

19:33.046 --> 19:36.799
I'LL TURN THE LIGHT OUT
IN A MINUTE.

19:36.967 --> 19:39.218
NO. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

19:39.386 --> 19:41.929
I'M NOT SLEEPY.

19:43.640 --> 19:45.975
AFTER ALL THAT TRAVEL?

19:46.143 --> 19:48.853
COME ON. WHO ARE YOU
WORRIED ABOUT NOW?

19:49.021 --> 19:50.646
NO ONE.

19:50.814 --> 19:52.940
YOU SURE?

19:53.108 --> 19:54.609
SURE.

19:57.654 --> 20:01.616
GOOD NIGHT.

20:10.834 --> 20:13.586
REVEREND! REVEREND!

20:25.766 --> 20:27.225
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

20:27.392 --> 20:28.351
COME IN.

20:28.518 --> 20:29.685
MARY?

20:29.853 --> 20:31.103
OH, HI, MA.

20:31.271 --> 20:35.483
HI. WELL, I JUST FOUND OUT
ABOUT TOMORROW'S PICNIC.

20:35.651 --> 20:37.360
IT WAS
THE CHILDREN'S IDEA.

20:37.527 --> 20:39.779
THEY WANTED TO DO
SOMETHING SPECIAL FOR YOU.

20:39.947 --> 20:43.783
ADAM SEEMED ALMOST
AS EXCITED AS THEY WERE.

20:43.951 --> 20:45.743
DIDN'T PA COME WITH YOU?

20:45.911 --> 20:48.746
NO. NO. HE STOPPED BY
THE CHURCH TO, UH...

20:48.914 --> 20:52.667
TO DISCUSS THE SERVICE
WITH REVEREND CORLISS.

20:52.834 --> 20:54.877
I BROUGHT YOU
SOMETHING.

20:55.045 --> 20:56.879
WHAT IS IT?

20:57.047 --> 20:59.173
COME AND FIND OUT.

21:06.265 --> 21:09.642
OK, NOW,
LET ME HOLD IT UP
AGAINST YOU.

21:19.987 --> 21:21.320
MA?

21:22.823 --> 21:24.407
IT'S YOUR WEDDING GOWN.

21:24.574 --> 21:27.034
UH-HUH.
YOURS NOW.

21:27.202 --> 21:29.036
DON'T CRY.
WHAT DID YOU THINK

21:29.204 --> 21:31.789
YOU WERE GOING TO
GET MARRIED IN?

21:31.957 --> 21:35.334
I WAS JUST GOING TO
WEAR MY GOOD DRESS.

21:35.502 --> 21:38.587
COME ON, NOW.
LET'S SLIP IT ON.

21:38.755 --> 21:40.464
I'LL SEE HOW IT
FITS.

21:40.632 --> 21:41.757
MARY?

21:41.925 --> 21:43.259
MARY.

21:43.427 --> 21:46.595
MARY,
WHAT'S WRONG?

21:46.763 --> 21:48.848
[SOBBING]

21:49.016 --> 21:50.433
OH...

21:53.103 --> 21:54.937
TELL ME, CHILD.

21:55.105 --> 21:58.232
I KNEW THERE
WAS SOMETHING.

22:00.527 --> 22:02.236
MA, I...

22:02.404 --> 22:04.780
I'M AFRAID.

22:06.033 --> 22:08.367
ARE YOU NERVOUS
ABOUT THE WEDDING?

22:08.535 --> 22:11.495
MOST PEOPLE
USUALLY ARE.

22:11.663 --> 22:13.539
NO.

22:13.707 --> 22:16.500
WELL,
WHAT IS IT, THEN?

22:20.547 --> 22:22.673
IT'S HARD TO EXPLAIN.

22:25.260 --> 22:27.136
WHATEVER IT IS,

22:27.304 --> 22:29.805
HAVE YOU TALKED
TO ADAM ABOUT IT?

22:29.973 --> 22:31.474
NO.

22:31.641 --> 22:33.601
YOU SHOULD,
YOU KNOW.

22:35.687 --> 22:37.980
I DON'T WANT TO
HURT HIM.

22:38.148 --> 22:41.025
HOW CAN TALKING OUT
YOUR PROBLEMS

22:41.193 --> 22:44.111
WITH SOMEONE
YOU LOVE HURT THEM?

22:48.784 --> 22:51.452
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE RIGHT.

22:52.829 --> 22:55.164
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'LL TALK TO HIM TONIGHT.

22:55.332 --> 22:57.166
OH, GOOD. GOOD.

22:57.334 --> 22:58.793
MMM!

22:58.960 --> 23:00.503
NOW...

23:00.670 --> 23:05.132
LET'S TRY THIS ON
AND SEE HOW IT FITS.

23:28.782 --> 23:31.951
I'VE GOT
ALL THE KIDS IN BED.

23:32.119 --> 23:33.744
MARY?

23:35.372 --> 23:36.705
I'M HERE, ADAM.

23:36.873 --> 23:39.417
I'M SORRY.
WERE YOU ASLEEP?

23:39.584 --> 23:41.085
NO.

23:41.253 --> 23:44.547
WHY DIDN'T YOU
ANSWER ME?

23:44.714 --> 23:46.340
I DON'T KNOW.

23:46.508 --> 23:49.051
OH, COME ON NOW.
WHAT IS IT?

23:49.219 --> 23:51.011
YOU'RE NOT HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS

23:51.179 --> 23:53.347
ABOUT BEING MARRIED
TO ME ALREADY, ARE YOU?

23:53.515 --> 23:57.977
WHY, MARY, YOU'D HAVE TO
BE BLIND NOT TO WANT TO
MARRY A MAN LIKE ME.

24:08.780 --> 24:11.449
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
I WAS IN THE ROOM,
DID YOU?

24:11.616 --> 24:13.534
WELL, NO, BUT--

24:13.702 --> 24:16.078
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THAT MEANS, BUT I DIDN'T.

24:16.246 --> 24:18.414
IT MEANS IF
WE HAD A CHILD...

24:18.582 --> 24:22.293
AND THAT CHILD
WANDERED AWAY
OR GOT IN TROUBLE--

24:22.461 --> 24:24.336
HEY, SLOW DOWN.

24:24.504 --> 24:25.963
WE'RE NOT EVEN
MARRIED YET,

24:26.131 --> 24:28.257
AND YOU'RE ALREADY
TALKING ABOUT PROBLEMS
WITH CHILDREN.

24:28.425 --> 24:30.259
DON'T YOU WANT
CHILDREN?

24:30.427 --> 24:32.136
WELL, OF COURSE I DO.

24:32.304 --> 24:34.722
WHAT IS THIS
ALL OF A SUDDEN?

24:34.890 --> 24:36.682
I MEAN, HOW MANY
CHILDREN DO YOU WANT?

24:36.850 --> 24:39.101
WE'VE GOT MORE THAN
20 HERE AT THE SCHOOL.

24:39.269 --> 24:40.936
WE HANDLE THEM ALL RIGHT.

24:41.104 --> 24:42.605
THEY'RE BLIND, TOO.

24:42.772 --> 24:46.025
THEY'RE NOT GOING
TO JUST WANDER OFF
BY THEMSELVES.

24:46.193 --> 24:50.196
WE CAN JUST FACE
THOSE PROBLEMS
WHEN THEY COME.

24:50.363 --> 24:51.822
NO.

24:51.990 --> 24:54.033
WE HAVE TO
FACE THEM NOW.

24:54.201 --> 24:56.994
WELL, HOW ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO THAT?

24:59.998 --> 25:01.457
MARY...

25:01.625 --> 25:04.668
I KNOW IT'S NOT
GOING TO BE EASY.

25:04.836 --> 25:07.421
I DON'T WANT TO
MARRY YOU.

25:11.968 --> 25:14.345
YOU DON'T MEAN THAT.
YOU JUST GOT YOURSELF--

25:14.513 --> 25:17.848
I DO MEAN THAT!
I DON'T WANT TO
MARRY YOU.

25:21.937 --> 25:23.771
MARY...

25:23.939 --> 25:27.942
MARY, EVERY DAY OF MY LIFE
SINCE I WENT BLIND,

25:28.109 --> 25:31.111
I'VE BEEN AFRAID
I COULDN'T HANDLE
WHAT MIGHT COME UP,

25:31.279 --> 25:35.699
BUT I KNOW THAT
WHAT I'M AFRAID OF,
IT'S NOT OUT THERE.

25:35.867 --> 25:37.576
IT'S INSIDE ME.

25:37.744 --> 25:40.621
AND IF THERE'S
SOMETHING THAT
I HAVE TO DO

25:40.789 --> 25:43.832
OR WANT TO DO, IT GETS
DONE BECAUSE I TRY.

25:44.000 --> 25:45.543
WELL, I CAN'T.

25:51.967 --> 25:54.635
LOOK, LET'S JUST TALK
ABOUT IT TOMORROW.

25:54.803 --> 25:56.637
THIS IS TOMORROW.

26:26.793 --> 26:30.546
YOU KNOW, THIS IS
REALLY FUNNY!

26:30.714 --> 26:34.341
I MEAN, ALL PARENTS
EVER PRAY FOR WHEN
THEY HAVE A CHILD

26:34.509 --> 26:36.218
IS THAT IT BE HEALTHY,

26:36.386 --> 26:41.807
AND WE CAN'T HAVE A CHILD
BECAUSE GOD MIGHT GIVE US
A HEALTHY ONE?

26:45.895 --> 26:50.733
MAYBE...MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST PRAY TO GOD AND ASK
HIM FOR A BLIND BABY

26:50.900 --> 26:54.528
SO WE COULD TAKE CARE OF IT
AND NOT HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT IT!

27:06.374 --> 27:08.250
DON'T SAY ANYTHING
TO THE CHILDREN

27:08.418 --> 27:10.878
UNTIL AFTER THE PICNIC
TOMORROW.

27:12.589 --> 27:14.381
THEY'VE DONE
SO MUCH PLANNING,

27:14.549 --> 27:18.385
THERE'S JUST NO REASON
TO SPOIL IT FOR THEM.

27:44.537 --> 27:46.580
[CRYING]

28:00.804 --> 28:03.514
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:03.682 --> 28:05.974
PROBABLY THAT
CIGAR-SMOKING
MANAGER

28:06.142 --> 28:08.435
CHECKING TO SEE
IF EVERYTHING'S
ALL RIGHT.

28:13.733 --> 28:15.109
ADAM?

28:17.320 --> 28:18.737
ADAM!

28:18.905 --> 28:20.614
HEY!

28:33.878 --> 28:36.130
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

28:36.297 --> 28:38.424
[PEOPLE CLAPPING]

29:54.709 --> 29:56.126
Girl: YAY!

29:56.294 --> 29:57.753
MORE, MR. INGALLS!

29:57.921 --> 29:59.379
PLEASE,
PLAY ANOTHER ONE.

29:59.547 --> 30:01.715
WHY DON'T YOU ALL PLAY
SOME GAMES RIGHT NOW?

30:01.883 --> 30:03.509
I'LL PLAY SOME MORE
LATER.

30:03.676 --> 30:06.637
UH, WHO WANTS TO BE
IN THE 3-LEGGED RACE?

30:06.805 --> 30:09.765
THE GIRLS WILL BEAT
THE BOYS!

30:29.118 --> 30:32.329
I COULDN'T STAND
TO JUST SIT THERE
WATCHING THEM.

30:32.497 --> 30:34.081
I KNOW.

30:37.126 --> 30:38.752
OH, CHARLES.

30:38.920 --> 30:41.964
IF ONLY THERE WAS
SOMETHING WE COULD
DO TO HELP THEM,

30:42.131 --> 30:45.384
TO HELP MARY
COME TO HER SENSES.

30:45.552 --> 30:49.429
IT'S THE SAME MARY
WE FIRST SAW
WHEN SHE WENT BLIND--

30:49.597 --> 30:51.473
INSIDE HERSELF,
SHUT AWAY.

30:51.641 --> 30:56.061
SHE CAME OUT OF IT
THAT TIME. MAYBE SHE'LL
COME OUT OF IT NOW.

30:56.229 --> 30:58.564
DEAR GOD, I HOPE SO.

30:58.731 --> 31:02.317
Man: HEYAH! HEYAH!

31:02.485 --> 31:04.111
[HOOFBEATS]

31:04.279 --> 31:05.487
HEYAH!

31:05.655 --> 31:07.573
[CATTLE MOOING]

31:11.828 --> 31:13.954
[MAN WHISTLING]

31:25.216 --> 31:26.508
Charles: WHAT'S GOING ON?

31:26.676 --> 31:29.386
DUST STORM. BAD ONE.
HEAD FOR COVER.

31:29.554 --> 31:32.180
LET'S GET THE CHILDREN
TO TOWN.

31:34.058 --> 31:36.351
[WIND HOWLING]

32:04.088 --> 32:06.256
[HORSE WHINNIES]

32:07.884 --> 32:09.968
Charles: COME ON, KIDS.

32:10.136 --> 32:12.638
Caroline: HOLD ON.

32:12.805 --> 32:14.765
Man: ALL RIGHT, COME ON.

32:14.933 --> 32:17.392
CAREFUL. HOLD ON.
HOLD HANDS.

32:17.560 --> 32:20.270
EVERYBODY TAKE A HAND.

32:23.066 --> 32:24.232
[GLASS BREAKS]

32:24.400 --> 32:26.443
Charles: TO THE RIGHT.

32:27.862 --> 32:30.989
GET EVERYBODY INSIDE!
I'LL GET THE TEAM
IN THE LIVERY!

32:31.157 --> 32:32.991
HERE.

32:40.959 --> 32:45.462
Man: HOLD ON. NOW,
WE'LL BE SAFE IN HERE
UNTIL THE STORM PASSES.

32:45.630 --> 32:46.838
IS EVERYBODY HERE?

32:47.006 --> 32:48.465
NOW...MARVIN COIL?

32:48.633 --> 32:49.424
HERE.

32:49.592 --> 32:50.634
ELIZABETH DEARBORN?

32:50.802 --> 32:51.718
HERE.

32:51.886 --> 32:52.761
TIM CAPER?
HERE.

32:52.929 --> 32:53.971
GEORGE ALLEN?

32:54.138 --> 32:54.972
HERE!

32:55.139 --> 32:56.306
WHERE'S SUSAN GOODSPEED?

32:56.474 --> 32:58.100
SUSAN GOODSPEED?

33:00.603 --> 33:04.064
Man: SUSAN!
SUSAN GOODSPEED!

33:05.566 --> 33:06.984
MARY, NO!

33:07.151 --> 33:08.902
WE HAVE TO FIND HER!

33:09.070 --> 33:10.737
WE WILL.

33:13.616 --> 33:16.118
Caroline: ADAM, WAIT!

33:17.328 --> 33:18.662
OH!

33:21.124 --> 33:22.499
MA!

33:27.964 --> 33:32.634
MRS. INGALLS!

33:33.928 --> 33:35.470
MR. AMES!

33:35.638 --> 33:36.638
[GLASS BREAKS]

33:36.806 --> 33:41.143
MR. AMES!

33:44.647 --> 33:47.649
Adam: IT'S MRS. INGALLS!
GET HER INSIDE!

33:47.817 --> 33:49.443
[GLASS BREAKS]

33:57.869 --> 33:59.995
MARY, GO INSIDE
WITH MR. AMES.

34:00.163 --> 34:01.079
NO!

34:01.247 --> 34:02.622
GO INSIDE!

34:02.790 --> 34:05.959
NO! THE CHILDREN ARE
MY RESPONSIBILITY, TOO!

34:08.629 --> 34:10.964
ALL RIGHT. COME ON.

34:19.682 --> 34:21.016
Mary: SUSAN!

34:21.184 --> 34:23.310
Adam: SUSAN!

34:26.105 --> 34:34.988
SUSAN!

34:38.409 --> 34:39.534
[GLASS BREAKS]

34:39.702 --> 34:41.161
[COUGHING]

34:45.374 --> 34:48.710
HERE. PUT THIS
OVER YOUR MOUTH.

34:48.878 --> 34:51.213
[COUGHING]

34:53.549 --> 34:56.218
ADAM,
WE'LL NEVER FIND HER!

34:56.385 --> 34:57.469
YES, WE WILL!

34:57.637 --> 35:00.013
NOW, THAT'S THE
DIFFERENCE BETWEEN US.

35:00.181 --> 35:02.766
IF THERE'S SOMETHING
I HAVE TO DO, I DO IT!

35:02.934 --> 35:04.601
I DON'T JUST GIVE UP!

35:04.769 --> 35:07.229
NEITHER DO I!

35:07.396 --> 35:09.481
[COUGHING]

35:14.695 --> 35:18.323
SUSAN!

35:18.491 --> 35:19.991
[CHARLES COUGHING]

35:20.159 --> 35:22.035
ALMOST DIDN'T
FIND MY WAY BACK.

35:22.203 --> 35:24.412
YOUR WIFE
HAS BEEN HURT.

35:28.126 --> 35:29.835
DEAR GOD, HONEY,
WHAT HAPPENED?

35:30.002 --> 35:33.421
NO, IT'S...IT'S NOT DEEP.
IT'S JUST A LOT OF BLOOD.

35:33.589 --> 35:35.715
LISTEN, SUSAN GOODSPEED
IS MISSING.

35:35.883 --> 35:38.552
WE TRIED TO GO FIND HER.
SOMETHING HIT ME.

35:38.719 --> 35:41.096
MARY AND ADAM
ARE OUT THERE.

35:52.441 --> 35:54.609
[GLASS BREAKS]

35:54.777 --> 35:56.236
ADAM!

35:59.115 --> 36:00.782
MARY!

36:07.498 --> 36:22.345
[MARY COUGHING]

36:24.724 --> 36:26.433
Susan, faintly:
I'M HERE!

36:26.601 --> 36:28.351
DO YOU HEAR
ANYTHING?

36:30.146 --> 36:32.480
NO!

36:32.648 --> 36:33.982
Susan: I'M HERE!

36:34.150 --> 36:35.650
I'M HERE!

36:35.818 --> 36:37.819
I CAN HEAR HER.

36:38.988 --> 36:41.990
I'M HERE!

36:43.409 --> 36:45.368
I'M HERE! I'M HERE!

36:45.536 --> 36:49.164
HERE! I'M HERE!
I'M HERE!

36:49.332 --> 36:54.336
I'M HERE! I'M HERE!
HERE! I'M HERE!

36:54.503 --> 36:58.882
HERE! I'M HERE! HERE!
I'M HERE!

36:59.050 --> 37:00.342
SUSAN?

37:00.509 --> 37:01.426
I'M HERE!

37:01.594 --> 37:02.844
IT'S ALL RIGHT!

37:03.012 --> 37:04.179
HERE! I'M HERE!

37:04.347 --> 37:06.223
IT'S ALL RIGHT, HONEY.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:06.390 --> 37:07.849
HERE! I'M HERE!
I'M HERE!

37:08.017 --> 37:09.684
IT'S ALL RIGHT NOW.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:09.852 --> 37:10.685
HERE! HERE!

37:10.853 --> 37:12.145
OK, OK.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:12.313 --> 37:15.190
I'M HERE! I'M HERE!

37:15.358 --> 37:16.566
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:16.734 --> 37:18.193
I'M HERE! I'M HERE!

37:18.361 --> 37:19.819
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT!

37:19.987 --> 37:21.196
LISTEN TO ME!
LISTEN TO ME.

37:21.364 --> 37:22.530
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT NOW.

37:22.698 --> 37:24.324
WE'RE HERE. WE'RE
WITH YOU, HONEY.

37:24.492 --> 37:25.951
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

37:26.118 --> 37:27.786
I WAS SO AFRAID!

37:27.954 --> 37:29.871
I THOUGHT I WAS
GOING TO DIE!

37:30.039 --> 37:31.623
OH, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:31.791 --> 37:32.874
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:33.042 --> 37:36.711
I DIDN'T THINK ANYONE
WAS GOING TO FIND ME!

37:36.879 --> 37:38.213
[CRYING]

37:38.381 --> 37:41.299
WHAT DID YOU THINK,
WE WERE GOING TO
LEAVE YOU OUT HERE?

37:41.467 --> 37:44.219
WE KNEW WE HAD TO
FIND YOU, AND WE DID.

37:44.387 --> 37:49.224
ALL A BODY HAS TO DO
IS SET THEIR MIND TO
SOMETHING AND THEN DO IT.

37:49.392 --> 37:50.809
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

37:50.977 --> 37:52.936
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.
WE FOUND YOU.

37:53.104 --> 37:55.480
WE FOUND YOU.

37:58.276 --> 37:59.859
HONEY...

38:00.027 --> 38:02.070
HONEY,
YOU STOP CRYING.

38:03.739 --> 38:06.032
I WANT TO
ASK YOU SOMETHING.

38:07.910 --> 38:11.579
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO BE THE FLOWER GIRL
AT MY WEDDING?

38:11.747 --> 38:13.623
I'D LIKE THAT.

38:13.791 --> 38:17.544
BOY, WOULD I LIKE THAT!

38:19.922 --> 38:25.260
THAT IS...IF IT'S
ALL RIGHT WITH YOU, ADAM.

38:25.428 --> 38:28.638
IT IS JUST GREAT
WITH ME.

38:38.399 --> 38:40.233
[LAUGHING]

38:40.401 --> 38:42.944
I LOVE YOU.

38:43.112 --> 38:44.362
OH, I LOVE YOU.

38:44.530 --> 38:46.740
[GLASS BREAKS]

38:46.907 --> 38:51.328
MARY!

38:54.623 --> 38:56.291
ADAM!

38:56.459 --> 38:59.794
Mary: IN HERE, PA!
IN HERE!

38:59.962 --> 39:01.504
MARY?

39:05.468 --> 39:06.718
MARY!

39:06.886 --> 39:09.888
Adam: UNDER
THE LOADING DOCK, SIR!

39:24.028 --> 39:27.113
I TAKE IT
EVERYTHING'S ALL RIGHT.

39:28.657 --> 39:30.617
[BOTH LAUGHING]

39:32.411 --> 39:34.704
Charles: WELL, IS IT ALL RIGHT
OR ISN'T IT?

39:34.872 --> 39:38.291
EVERYTHING'S FINE, PA.
JUST FINE.

39:44.465 --> 39:46.758
SHALL WE GO BACK
TO THE SCHOOL?

39:46.926 --> 39:48.051
UH-UH.

39:48.219 --> 39:51.930
WHAT? ON A BEAUTIFUL
DAY LIKE THIS?

40:21.544 --> 40:23.461
THAT'S THE LAST
OF THE CHAIRS.

40:23.629 --> 40:24.796
THANKS, MR. AMES.

40:24.964 --> 40:26.423
WELL, I BETTER GO
CHECK ON ADAM.

40:26.590 --> 40:28.967
HOW'S HE DOING?
A LITTLE NERVOUS?

40:29.135 --> 40:30.635
LET ME PUT IT
THIS WAY.

40:30.803 --> 40:34.055
HE'S HAVING TROUBLE
BREATHING, BUT IT'S NOT
FROM THE DUST.

40:34.223 --> 40:36.057
HA HA HA!

40:37.184 --> 40:39.811
AFRAID THE STORM KEPT
THE REVEREND ALDEN.

40:39.979 --> 40:42.689
WELL, YOU WANT TO WAIT
A LITTLE LONGER?

40:42.857 --> 40:45.066
HE MIGHT STILL GET HERE.
I KNOW HOW MARY FEELS.

40:45.234 --> 40:48.361
NO. SHE DOESN'T
KNOW ABOUT IT, SO SHE
WON'T BE DISAPPOINTED.

40:48.529 --> 40:50.405
I'D TAKE IT KINDLY
IF YOU'D GO AHEAD

40:50.573 --> 40:52.449
WITH THE ARRANGEMENTS
THEY MADE WITH YOU.

40:52.616 --> 40:54.159
I'LL BE HAPPY TO.

40:54.326 --> 40:58.037
WE'LL JUST TAKE THINGS
AS THEY ARE, INCLUDING
THE DUST, I FEAR.

40:58.205 --> 41:00.623
NOT MUCH WE CAN
DO ABOUT IT.

41:01.750 --> 41:04.252
OH! IT'S NO USE,
MARY.

41:04.420 --> 41:08.006
I CAN BRUSH AND BRUSH,
AND THE DUST IS STILL THERE.

41:08.174 --> 41:10.091
I CAN FEEL IT
UNDER MY SKIN, MA.

41:10.259 --> 41:12.010
I DOUBT THAT ADAM
WILL MIND.

41:12.178 --> 41:13.928
I CAN JUST SEE
THE WEDDING STORY:

41:14.096 --> 41:17.182
"THE BRIDE WORE
A CHARMING LAYER
OF DUST."

41:17.349 --> 41:18.433
HA HA HA!

41:18.601 --> 41:20.935
MY MARY'S BACK
TO HERSELF AGAIN!

41:21.103 --> 41:22.270
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

41:22.438 --> 41:23.771
Charles:
YOU LADIES DECENT?

41:23.939 --> 41:25.982
WELL, AS DECENT
AS CAN BE.

41:27.276 --> 41:29.527
REVEREND CORLISS
IS READY.

41:32.323 --> 41:34.616
YOU'RE AS PRETTY
AS A PICTURE.

41:34.783 --> 41:36.743
GOD BLESS.

41:39.079 --> 41:41.414
SEE YOU IN THERE.

41:46.962 --> 41:51.591
THIS IS IT.

41:55.638 --> 41:58.640
I LOVE YOU.

42:01.894 --> 42:03.770
SUSAN, WE'RE READY.

42:14.490 --> 42:17.158
[PLAYING "WEDDING MARCH"]

43:00.703 --> 43:02.328
[MUSIC STOPS]

43:18.721 --> 43:21.848
Reverend Corliss:
WHO GIVES THIS WOMAN TO BE WED?

43:22.891 --> 43:25.018
HER MOTHER AND I DO.

43:28.606 --> 43:30.064
DEARLY BELOVED,

43:30.232 --> 43:32.900
WE ARE GATHERED HERE
IN THE SIGHT OF GOD

43:33.068 --> 43:35.111
AND IN THE PRESENCE
OF THESE WITNESSES

43:35.279 --> 43:40.908
TO JOIN TOGETHER
THIS MAN AND THIS WOMAN
IN HOLY MATRIMONY,

43:41.076 --> 43:43.536
WHICH IS
AN HONORABLE ESTATE...

43:46.373 --> 43:50.710
INSTITUTED OF GOD
AND SIGNIFYING UNTO US

43:50.878 --> 43:56.424
THE MYSTICAL UNION
THAT EXISTS BETWEEN
CHRIST AND HIS CHURCH.

43:56.592 --> 43:59.344
Reverend Alden:
INTO THIS HOLY ESTATE,

43:59.511 --> 44:03.598
THESE TWO PERSONS COME NOW
TO BE JOINED.

44:07.102 --> 44:10.355
IF ANY MAN HERE
CAN SHOW JUST CAUSE

44:10.522 --> 44:14.150
WHY THESE TWO SHOULD NOT
LAWFULLY BE JOINED TOGETHER,

44:14.318 --> 44:19.030
LET HIM NOW SPEAK
OR FOREVER HEREAFTER
HOLD HIS PEACE.

44:22.409 --> 44:28.539
ADAM, WILT THOU TAKE THIS WOMAN
TO BE THY WEDDED WIFE,

44:28.707 --> 44:32.460
TO LIVE TOGETHER
IN HOLY MATRIMONY?

44:32.628 --> 44:37.423
WILT THOU LOVE HER,
HONOR AND KEEP HER,

44:37.591 --> 44:40.802
IN SICKNESS AND IN HEALTH,

44:40.969 --> 44:43.304
AND, FORSAKING ALL OTHERS,

44:43.472 --> 44:47.350
CLEAVE THEE ONLY TO HER
AS LONG AS YE BOTH SHALL LIVE?

44:47.518 --> 44:49.435
I WILL.

44:51.730 --> 44:53.523
AND, MARY...

44:53.691 --> 44:57.485
WILL YOU TAKE THIS MAN
TO BE YOUR WEDDED HUSBAND,

44:57.653 --> 45:00.655
TO LIVE TOGETHER
IN HOLY MATRIMONY?

45:00.823 --> 45:06.411
WILL YOU LOVE HIM,
HONOR AND KEEP HIM,

45:06.578 --> 45:09.956
IN SICKNESS AND IN HEALTH,

45:10.124 --> 45:12.542
AND, FORSAKING ALL OTHERS,

45:12.710 --> 45:17.463
CLEAVE THEE ONLY UNTO HIM
AS LONG AS YE BOTH SHALL LIVE?

45:19.550 --> 45:21.884
I WILL.

45:32.062 --> 45:37.150
THE WEDDING RING IS
THE OUTWARD AND VISIBLE SIGN

45:37.317 --> 45:41.779
OF AN INWARD
AND SPIRITUAL GIFT.

45:41.947 --> 45:47.368
IT SIGNIFIES TO ALL
THAT THIS MAN AND THIS WOMAN

45:47.536 --> 45:50.621
HAVE JOINED TOGETHER
IN HOLY MATRIMONY

45:50.789 --> 45:54.625
THROUGH THE CHURCH OF OUR LORD
JESUS CHRIST.

45:54.793 --> 45:57.170
SHALL WE PRAY?

45:59.214 --> 46:02.091
BLESS, O LORD,
THIS GIVING OF THIS RING,

46:02.259 --> 46:07.096
THAT HE WHO GIVES IT
AND SHE WHO WEARS IT

46:07.264 --> 46:10.349
MAY DWELL FOREVER
IN THY PEACE

46:10.517 --> 46:13.436
AND CONTINUE IN THY FAVOR,

46:13.604 --> 46:17.273
THROUGH JESUS CHRIST
OUR LORD. AMEN.

46:35.417 --> 46:38.753
IN TOKEN AND PLEDGE

46:38.921 --> 46:43.424
OF OUR CONSTANT FAITH
AND ABIDING LOVE,

46:43.592 --> 46:45.927
I THEE WED...

46:46.094 --> 46:51.933
IN THE NAME OF
THE FATHER AND THE SON
AND THE HOLY SPIRIT.

46:53.560 --> 46:56.813
Reverend: INASMUCH AS
ADAM AND MARY

46:56.980 --> 47:00.566
HAVE CONSENTED TOGETHER
IN HOLY WEDLOCK

47:00.734 --> 47:03.110
AND HAVE WITNESSED
THE SAME BEFORE GOD

47:03.278 --> 47:05.655
AND THIS COMPANY

47:05.823 --> 47:08.157
AND HAVE PLEDGED
THEIR FAITH,

47:08.325 --> 47:10.159
EACH TO THE OTHER,

47:10.327 --> 47:13.621
AND HAVING DECLARED THE CASE
BY JOINING HANDS

47:13.789 --> 47:16.123
AND THE GIVING AND THE RECEIVING
OF THIS RING,

47:16.291 --> 47:19.168
I NOW PRONOUNCE YOU
HUSBAND AND WIFE TOGETHER

47:19.336 --> 47:22.630
IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER
AND OF THE SON

47:22.798 --> 47:25.967
AND OF THE
HOLY SPIRIT. AMEN.

47:27.803 --> 47:31.639
AND WHOM GOD HATH
JOINED TOGETHER,

47:31.807 --> 47:34.851
LET NO MAN PUT ASUNDER.

47:37.813 --> 47:40.022
YOU MAY KISS THE BRIDE.

47:49.324 --> 47:51.826
[WHISPERING]
I love you.

47:51.994 --> 47:54.620
I love you.
